    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Hungarian Chamber to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 27 June
                    1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Kamarjay chased them most recently a few days ago, but
                            they could not pay him, in the end Ferenc Újlaki arranged for him to
                            receive 200 florins on the condition that he will be satisfied with it
                            and wait for the King to return and resolve his difficulties. Tamás
                            Kamarjay had already written about these difficulties to the Controller
                            while Albert Peregi was alive, as well as to the late Pál Várday, so
                            that Várday and Oláh can inform the King about it together. However, as
                            far as they can see, nothing has been done about it, so they are asking
                            Oláh to get an answer from the King, although the Chamber cannot meet
                            such a debt because it has hardly any revenue.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad dominum cancellarium.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Reverendissime Domine, Domine et Patrone Observandissime,
                    servitiorum nostrorum commendationem!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Proxime praeteritis diebus cum instaret nobis dominus
                        <persName>Thomas Kamariai</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Tamás
                        Kamarjay.</note> et propter causas eas, quae certa descriptione contuentur,
                    nihil ei <del corresp="author">dare</del><add corresp="author" type="corr"
                        >numerare</add> possemus, effecit tandem reverendissimus dominus
                        <persName>Iaurensis</persName><note xml:id="note.2">Ferenc Újlaki.</note>
                    locumtenens regiae maiestatis, ut <del corresp="author">sub</del> Florenorum
                    ducentos daremus ea lege, ut contentus his exspectaret reditum simul et
                    resolutionem regiae maiestatis, domini nostri clementissimi de difficultatibus
                    illis descriptis, quas olim vivente quondam reverendo domino <persName>Alberto
                        praeposito</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Albert Peregi died in
                        1546.</note> Camerae praefecto dominus magister rationum<note
                        xml:id="note.4">Ferenc Kisserényi (†ca.1560) was Pál Várday’s retainer <hi
                            rend="italic">(familiaris)</hi> and a Controller of the Hungarian
                        Chamber in 1528–1529 and 1531–1549, see <hi rend="smallcap">Szabó-Turákné
                            Póka</hi> 2021, 261–262; and <hi rend="smallcap">Remete</hi> 1963,
                        145.</note> conscripserat, ac reverendissimo olim domino
                        <persName>Strigoniensi</persName><note xml:id="note.5">Pál Várday died in
                        1549.</note> privatim ita dederat, ut ille <add corresp="author"
                        type="insert">una</add> cum Reverendissima Dominatione Vestra maiestatem
                    regiam de illis informaret ac resolutionem suae maiestatis <del corresp="author"
                        >ea re de</del> scripto ad Cameram daret. Nondum autem intelligimus ullam
                    esse difficultatem illarum <del corresp="author">resolutioni</del><add
                        corresp="author" type="corr">resolutionum</add> factam et nihilominus
                    dominus <persName>Kamariai</persName> nos urget immemor conditionis sibi coram
                    domino <persName>locumtenente</persName> declaratae. Rogamus praeterim
                    Reverendissimam Dominationem Vestram, ut ubi maiestas regia sacra redierit,
                    velit a sua maiestate certum responsum accipere, stantibus <del corresp="author"
                        >siquidem</del> enim et non resolutis illis difficultatibus antiquis non
                    habet Camera modum, quo ipsi <persName>Camariai</persName> satisfaciat, licet
                    alioqui ex pecunia contributionis (quae rebus turbatis spe omnium minor esse
                    cepit) nihil in huiusmodi vetera debita solvi posset. Maiestate regia hoc ipsum
                    expresse prohibere, ceteri autem proventus Camerae, hoc est tricesimales, adeo
                    sunt tenues, ut vix ad quotidianas et occidentales necessitates <del
                        corresp="author">expeditum</del> sufficiant. Reverendissimam Dominationem
                    Vestram optamus valere feliciter.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Posonii</placeName> die 27. Iunii anno Domini 1552.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">
                    <seg type="signature">Reverendissimae Dominationis Vestrae deditissimi
                        servitores.</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
